  "prompt": "Do middle class people shop at thrift stores?",
  "response": "Yes, middle-class people do shop at thrift stores for a variety of reasons. Thrift stores offer a chance to find unique, high-quality items at significantly lower prices compared to retail stores. Shoppers can find gently used clothing, furniture, home d\u00e9cor, and other goods that might otherwise be out of their budget if purchased new. Additionally, many middle-class individuals are conscious of sustainability and prefer the eco-friendly option of buying second-hand items. The appeal of getting a good deal, supporting charitable causes, and reducing waste also drives middle-class shoppers to patronize thrift stores.",
